  EFR 2 Linux
  -----------

1. Start EFR

Make run.sh file executable

    chmod +x run.sh

Execute run.sh file

    ./run.sh



2. Install as service

Change these lines in file efr.service to execute run.sh in your path as your user:

    User=efr
    ExecStart=/path/to/EFR/run.sh

Copy file efr.service to /etc/systemd/system/

    sudo cp efr.service /etc/systemd/system/



3. Control service

start efr

    sudo systemctl start efr

stop efr

    sudo systemctl stop efr

enable automatic start on boot

    sudo systemctl enable efr

disable automatic start on boot

    sudo systemctl disable efr
